line_1: 'Tis all by luck that things are carry'd —
line_2: He'll suffer for it when he's marry'd.

line_1: So, to the neighbouring meadow carry'd,
line_2: A formal ass the couple marry'd.

line_1: So with decorum all things carry'd;
line_2: Miss frown'd, and blush'd, and then was — married.

line_1: Letters and houses by an angel carried;
line_2: And, wondrous! virgin nuns to JESUS married.

line_1: Their Jugg was to the Ringers carry'd;
line_2: Who ever either Dy'd, or Marry'd.
